This specific block of code is where you establish the "Handshake" between your Python program and the S3 service running in your container
 It creates a persistent connection object that you will use later to upload or download files.

>. endpoint_url=endpoint_url
The Action: Directs the traffic to a specific address.
The Meaning: This is the most critical line for your local setup. By default, boto3 tries to connect to the actual AWS cloud (e.g., s3.amazonaws.com). Since your S3 is in a container (LocalStack or MinIO), you are overriding that destination to point to your local machine (e.g., http://localhost:4566).

>. aws_access_key_id="test"
Provides the "Username."

>. aws_secret_access_key="test"
Provides the "Password."
This is the cryptographic key paired with your ID. Again.

>. region_name="us-east-1"
Defines the geographical "Data Center" location.

