>.  The key (The Identifier)
Must be a String (str).

Why? The key is literally the "Object Name" or "URL Path." Since S3 is a REST-based service, the key becomes part of the URL.

Format: It should follow standard web naming conventions (avoid special characters like ?, #, or [).

Correct: "my_folder/ai_result_01.json"

Incorrect: 12345 (Integer) — you must wrap it in str(12345).

>.  The data (The Payload)
The Body parameter in put_object is more flexible but generally accepts three main types:

A. String (str)
Usage: Best for your AI-generated sentences or raw text.

Note: Boto3 will automatically encode this into bytes (usually UTF-8) before sending it over the wire.

B. Bytes (bytes)
Usage: Best for images, PDF files, or encrypted data.

Example: b"This is a byte string" or the output of file.read().

C. File-like Object (Streaming)
Usage: Best for very large files (like a 500MB ML model).

Example: An open file handle like open('large_data.bin', 'rb').

Benefit: It "streams" the data from your Mac's disk to the S3 container without loading the whole 500MB into your RAM first.